    vocalGenderCodes: 'Male rock vocals range from baritone growl to tenor belt to falsetto. Female rock vocals have carved space from powerful belting (Heart, Paramore) to understated delivery (Mazzy Star, Snail Mail). The "rock voice" was historically coded masculine \u2014 raspy, aggressive, loud \u2014 but this has been consistently subverted.',
