    vocalGenderCodes: 'Folk vocal conventions are relatively open \u2014 women and men sing in their natural voices without genre-imposed modifications. The "folk voice" prioritizes clarity and storytelling ability over gendered vocal qualities. High male voices (falsetto), low female voices, and everything between are accepted.',
    physicalityInPerformance: "Minimal and non-gendered \u2014 the performer sits or stands with an instrument. Physical display is not part of folk performance convention. The body is present as a voice-producing instrument, not as a spectacle. This creates an inherently more gender-equal performance space.",
