    vocalGenderCodes: "Male artists dominate commercial Afrobeats with melodic singing and toasting styles. Female artists like Tems, Tiwa Savage, and Ayra Starr have carved distinctive vocal spaces \u2014 often with softer, more R&B-inflected delivery that contrasts with male bravado without being subordinate to it.",
    physicalityInPerformance: "Dance is non-negotiable in Afrobeats performance. Specific dance moves become viral trends (Zanku, Legwork, Palliative). The body's relationship to the beat \u2014 how waist movement, footwork, and shoulder rolls interact with percussion layers \u2014 is the genre's primary physical language.",
